import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['size'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.75)
    plt.axvline(data['size'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Node Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of node sizes in the tree?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.boxplot(data['size'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['size'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-', label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average size of nodes in the tree?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Node Size')
    plt.ylabel('Size')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['parent'], bins=30, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['parent'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['parent'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Parent Node Identifiers')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of parent node identifiers in the tree?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts().sort_values(ascending=False)
    top_names = name_counts[:10]
    ax = top_names.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Node Names')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common node name in the tree?')
    for i in ax.patches:
        ax.text(i.get_x(), i.get_height()+10, str(round(i.get_height(), 2)), fontsize=10, color='black')
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.xlabel('Parent Node Identifier')

    plt.title('What is the relationship between node size and parent node identifier?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
